<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-53-0824 </DOCNO><TEXT>Cluster analysis is used to group into regions over West Africa, a climaticdata set which had been previously reduced to four factors. The regionsthus derived are more firmly climate based than is the case with previousclassifications. Various degrees of generality are also achieved by themethods, ranging from five regions at the primary level to twenty regionsfor more detailed work. Overall, a ten-region climatic cluster is foundto be optimal for most purposes.</TEXT></DOC>